Subtitle
17 TO AMEND THE SALES TAX EXEMPTION FOR
18 AIRCRAFT HELD FOR RESALE AND USED FOR
19 RENTAL OR CHARTER; AND TO CLARIFY THE
20 PERSONS ELIGIBLE FOR THE SALES TAX
21 EXEMPTION FOR AIRCRAFT HELD FOR RESALE
22 AND USED FOR RENTAL OR CHARTER.
23
24 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
25
26 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code ยง 26-52-409(a), concerning the sales tax
27 exemption for aircraft held for resale and used for rental or charter, is
28 amended to read as follows:
29 (a)(1) Any person, whether an established business or an individual,
30 that is engaged in the business of selling aircraft in this state, and
31 holding holds a retail sales tax permit, and holds aircraft in stock for
32 resale may purchase aircraft exempt for resale and use the aircraft for
33 rental or charter service without payment of sales or use tax for a period of
34 not to exceed one (1) year from the date of purchase of the aircraft.
35 (2) In the case of aircraft purchased for resale which require
36 substantial modification or substantial refurbishing prior to resale, the
